cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed simplifications for gradient calculation could also suggest it belongs to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of the CREMI neuron segmentation challenge could suggest it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
